l Aviation Authority, closing the western Tehran FIR from May 22 20:46Z to May 25 08:30Z with limited daylight exceptions and fresh CAA approval required. The defense's own source confirms a western‑FIR suspension with limited exceptions, while denying only a newer nationwide notice. Under the rule, a broad suspension in a major Iranian airspace region with limited exceptions qualifies as a major non‑weather closure, so the proposition is more likely true than not.\"\n\nNow we need to call mcp with tool aar_submit_council_vote and args JSON string.\n\nBut first maybe we should verify evidence IDs? Not needed for vote, but we could optionally read some evidence to ensure we have correct details. However the instruction says we may use Pi's ordinary local tools to organize and analyze the record, but vote must rely on admitted record evidence. We have enough.\n\nWe'll call submit_council_vote.\n\n","contentIndex":0,"partial":{"api":"openai-completions","content":[{"thinking":"","thinkingSignature":"reasoning","type":"thinking"},{"arguments":{"args":"{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The admitted record shows multiple corroborating secondary reports of NOTAM OIIX A1010/26 issued by Iran's Civil Aviation Authority, closing the western Tehran FIR from May 22 20:46Z to May 25 08:30Z with limited daylight exceptions and fresh CAA approval required. The defense's own source confirms a western‑FIR suspension with limited exceptions, while denying only a newer nationwide notice. Under the rule, a broad suspension in a major Iranian airspace region with limited exceptions qualifies as a major non‑weather closure, so the proposition is more likely true than not.\"}","tool":"aar_submit_council_vote"},"id":"call_335f40fc6cfe47fb8ec2a435","name":"mcp","type":"toolCall"}],"model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","provider":"openrouter","responseId":"gen-1782834302-IoDU34mQ4jlkmcAxxHXS","responseModel":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b-20230311","role":"assistant","stop